<br>
  If I'm running a raid where there is the slightest possiblity of a pet causing a wipe-out, I will ask all pet-classes to not pet up.  The things that determines this for me?  AE attacks or extremely poor pathing.<br>
<br>
  If you don't like it, that's your perogative, but pet up after I've asked you not to and you'll be given a &quot;Thanks for your help&quot; and a TL to the portal of your choice.<br>
<br>
  Yes, there are characters out there I'd trust to pet up in ANY suituation.  Bobbo, Lizelle, Yppans, Tyrsis, Soulraven, Bookoo to name but a few.  But I can not count on people I don't know to have the level of judgement that these people have... and they NEVER pet up of their own accord in areas that I'd consider risky to do so because they know their own limitations.<br>
<br>
  Please note, I haven't lead a pick-up raid in years, and I'm not likely to anytime soon.  But the bottom line is this:<br>
<br>
  My raid, my rules.  Don't like it?  Start organising your own raids.<br>
<br>
